comments: Curry (GSW) legally contests Walker IV's (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Walker IV (LAL) legally contests Thompson's (GSW) jump shot attempt.
Curry (GSW) is retreating alongside James' (LAL) path and he absorbs the contact as they come together at the same spot.
Curry (GSW) reaches across James' (LAL) body and makes contact with James' arm and shoulder, which affects the driving shot attempt.
Wiggins (GSW) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Reaves (LAL) avoids contact with Curry (GSW) as Curry slips by during the driving shot attempt.
Moody (GSW) brings his arm forward towards Schroder (LAL) during his rip-through.
Davis (LAL) establishes himself in Moody's (GSW) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Wiggins (GSW) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Reaves (LAL) moves forward into Curry's (GSW) body and initiates contact as Curry is securing the rebound.
Wiggins (GSW) firms up on his left foot in James' (LAL) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Curry (GSW) loses control of the ball on his own accord and Davis (LAL) legally attempts to reach for the ball while it is loose.
After Wiggins (GSW) deflects the rebound away from James (LAL), Green (GSW) releases from the mutual engagement with Schroder (LAL) to retrieve the rebound.
Davis (LAL) legally contests Curry's (GSW) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Curry (GSW) does not overtly or abruptly extend his leg into Davis (LAL) after the release of his jump shot.
Moody (GSW) commits a take foul on Walker IV (LAL).
Schroder (LAL) is moving alongside Green's (GSW) path and marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
James (LAL) and Wiggins (GSW) tie each other up off-ball, and neither of them is close enough to get to the pass.
James (LAL) attempts to call a timeout, which is not recognized by the crew.

Wiggins (GSW) and Thompson (GSW) both make clean contact with the ball when they tie up Davis (LAL). However, Wiggins' right foot is out of bounds while he is in contact with the ball, and possession should have been awarded to LAL instead of a jump ball.
James (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball as Curry (GSW) returns to the floor and drops.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Replay review of the out of bounds called on Curry (GSW) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Curry is the last player to touch the ball and possession is correctly awarded to LAL.
Moody (GSW) and Reaves (LAL) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs during the inbound.
Thompson (GSW) attempts to disrupt the inbound pass to Reaves (LAL), who secures the ball as the clock runs out.
